Starbucks coffee is still one of the Uber coffee shops. The problem is in their management area. When there is an issue with too many employees, it usually starts at the top. They need to restructure the managers and work from there. When managers start becoming "besties" with the employees, customer service becomes selective and there is no one there to stop this. Much like Wal-Mart, the service has become deplorable. This is for way more than just 1 location. Had it been just one, I would focus on that one. However, it's happening across the country. This I have 1st hand knowledge of.

Worst Starbucks experience I've had in awhile.  I'm from pinellas county, a Starbucks gold member since 2010, and visit various locations every morning depending on my commute, between largo and tarpon springs. Today I was in the west Tampa area and looked up this location as it was closest in proximity. Went through the drive-thru and the girl got the sizes of my drinks wrong. Went back in to get two venti cups of ice, and here's where I confused them... I asked for more classic and a little cream in both cups of ice.. I was doing this so they wouldn't have to remake two quad espresso drinks. I then received two full venti cups of half and half. Not wanting to pour all of that into the trash I then had to ask them to pour some out so I could fit my original drink in the cup. When I did this I realized they put WAY too much classic in the cup of cream, thus ruined two drinks. Finally I asked to just have them remade.  All this time I was still waiting for one blueberry muffin as well. Still baffled on how little they cared/paid attention to how much they were wasting let alone not actually listening to the customer, they definitely were not busy, it was noon. I did not see a manager anywhere either, nor did anyone ever apologize. Best part is when one employee asked what I was still waiting on, I told him one muffin, he then disappeared until we were out the door. WOW STARBUCKS.
